      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PANNONIA (1) held a forward position from the pinch but drifted out of the finish when 6th at Q Parklands in a Maiden. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Tough to beat if on-song. LUNAR LIL (8) is overdue for a maiden success having placed at four of 12 starts and finishing in the money again at this track. Was prominent throughout latest and faded only late. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can feature again. SATISFIED (7) has found the minor placings here at last couple of runs, finishing third last time beaten 2.25 lengths (19.60). Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Well placed and gets his chance. LAUREN'S BABY (4) has top-three aspirations after placing at big odds last time.",
